{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Guarantee a penalty-free transfer for LISA holders before its replacement",
        "additional_details": "The Government has announced that the LISA is being replaced by a new type of ISA in 2028. We believe thousands of holders are feeling trapped by the \u00a3450,000 property cap, unchanged since 2017. The average London house price exceeds \u00a3551,000. Withdrawing triggers a 25% penalty \u2014 removing not just the government bonus but also 6.25% of savers' own money.\r\n\r\nIn our view these savers followed government guidance and did nothing wrong. We call for the Government to legislate for a penalty-free transfer window before 2028 so no saver loses their own money.\r\n",
        "background": "Government to formally confirm and legislate for a penalty-free transfer window for all current Lifetime ISA holders, allowing them to move their savings into the new ISA (as announced in 2025 budget)\u2014 or an alternative savings product \u2014 without incurring any withdrawal penalty by April 2028.",
